article.headline: SE Missouri 92, Tennessee St. 78
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Brandon Foust scored 20 points to lead Southeast Missouri State over Tennessee State 92-78 on Thursday. Southeast Missouri (7-12, 5-5 OVC) hit 10 3-pointers in the first half on their way to a 42-12 lead before Tennessee State rallied to trail 52-30 at halftime. The Redhawks cooled off in the second half, hitting only three 3-pointers, but maintained their lead with strong inside play. Michael Rembert had 13 points and 10 rebounds, and Dionte Perry added 15 points and eight rebounds for Southeast Missouri. Five players for Tennessee State (8-10, 4-4) scored in double figures, led by Andre Belton with 14. Reiley Ervin had 13, Ladarious Weaver had 12, Larry Turner had 11 and Clarence Mathews added 10 for the Tigers. David Johnson had 15 points and Marcus Rhodes had 12 for Missouri State, which also had five players in double figures.
